LIST OF PAPERS

In the beginning, there was CAM.  ExoCAM and its radiative transfer package
ExoRT arose from the ashes of Eric T. Wolf's graduate work on the Archean
Earth, and the faint young Sun paradox.  Over the years E.T. Wolf developed
CAM to use for paleoclimate and exoplanetary atmospheres.  ExoCAM and ExoRT
were formalized on Github for public use in the summer of 2019.  Below is a
list of papers published that directly use ExoCAM, ExoRT, and their ancestral
versions to conduct 3D climate simulations.  I do not include papers that used
CESM/CAM/WACCM, etc that do not formally use the ExoCAM package.

If you have a paper that you think belongs on this list, please contact me at
eric.wolf@colorado.edu.


Total Number (28)
Number by year
2020 (9)
2019 (9)
2018 (2)
2017 (3)
2016 (1) 
